To correctly compute the division of complex numbers, one must multiply both the numerator and the denominator by the conjugate of the denominator. Here, the conjugate of $2+i$ is $2-i$. The multiplication follows as: \begin{align*}
\frac{2-3i}{2+i} &= \frac{(2-3i)(2-i)}{(2+i)(2-i)}\\
&= \frac{4 - 2i - 6i + 3i^2}{4 - i^2}\\
&= \frac{4 - 8i - 3}{4 + 1}\\
&= \frac{1 - 8i}{5}\\
&= \boxed{\frac{1}{5} - \frac{8}{5}i}
\end{align*}
